                  </a>
                 </div>
                 <p class="tabs-home__imgstory">
                  <button class="button__prevstory nodesktop notablet" type="button">
                   <img alt="Show prev story" src="/SiteCollectionImages/OHCHR_images/fleche_slider_gauche.png"/>
                  </button>
                  <a href="https://www.ohchr.org/EN/NewsEvents/Pages/DisplayNews.aspx?NewsID=26921&amp;LangID=E">
                   <img alt="Families of people killed by police across the world report similar difficulties in their interactions with police and judicial authorities - Photo by Thais Do Rio on Unsplash" class="tabs-home__img" height="250" src="https://www.ohchr.org/SiteCollectionImages/Press/FightRacism_main.jpg" title="Families of people killed by police across the world report similar difficulties in their interactions with police and judicial authorities - Photo by Thais Do Rio on Unsplash" width="460"/>
                  </a>
                  <button class="button__nextstory nodesktop notablet" title="Show next story" type="button">
                   <img alt="Show next story" src="/SiteCollectionImages/OHCHR_images/fleche_slider_droite.png"/>
                  </button>
                 </p>
                 <p class="tabs-home__p">
                  The High Commissioner updated the Council on her report on systemic racism by law enforcement agencies, which was mandated after the killing of George Floyd. "Despite the heightened visibility around this issue, incidents of police brutality and racial discrimination against people of African descent continue to occur. It is imperative to end police violence," she said.

                 <p class="tabs-home__p">

                  <button class="button__nextstory nodesktop notablet" title="Show next story" type="button">

                 <p class="tabs-home__p">
                  On the International Day for the Elimination of Racial Discrimination (21 March) we celebrate the young human rights defenders who, through their global engagement for equality and inclusion, build solidarity, lead change and stand up against racism.

                  </a>

                   The water crisis has a “major impact on human rights” expert says
                  </a>
                 </div>
                 <p class="tabs-home__imgstory">
                  <button class="button__prevstory nodesktop notablet" type="button">
                   <img alt="Show prev story" src="/SiteCollectionImages/OHCHR_images/fleche_slider_gauche.png"/>

(Photo by Dipayan Bose / SOPA Images/Sipa USA)" class="tabs-home__img" height="250" src="https://www.ohchr.org/SiteCollectionImages/Press/012-Water_crisis.jpg" title="A view of the banks of holy river Ganga fully polluted by garbage. (Photo by Dipayan Bose / SOPA Images/Sipa USA)" width="460"/>
                  </a>
                  <button class="button__nextstory nodesktop notablet" title="Show next story" type="button">

                 </p>
                 <p class="tabs-home__p">

                  <br/>

                      <a class="ressource__titlelink big bl mh2-7e m0 aligntop" href="/EN/NewsEvents/Pages/DisplayNews.aspx?NewsID=26924&amp;LangID=E">
                       <strong>
                        Racial Discrimination
                       </strong>
                      </a>
                      The High Commissioner spoke at the General Assembly’s Commemoration of the International Day for the Elimination of Racial Discrimination.  “Racism violates everything we stand for and everything we do,” she said.
                      <br/>
                     </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="standard_carrousel_element mt2">
                     <div dir="ltr">
                      <a class="ressource__titlelink big bl mh2-7e m0 aligntop" href="/EN/NewsEvents/Pages/DisplayNews.aspx?NewsID=26921&amp;LangID=E">
                       <strong>
                        Systemic racism
                       </strong>
                      </a>
                      The High Commissioner updated the Council on her report on systemic racism by law enforcement agencies, which was mandated after the killing of George Floyd. “Despite the heightened visibility around this issue, incidents of police brutality and racial discrimination against people of African descent continue to occur. It is imperative to end police violence,” she said.
                      <br/>
                     </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="standard_carrousel_element mt2">
                     <div dir="ltr">
                      <a class="ressource__titlelink big bl mh2-7e m0 aligntop" href="/EN/NewsEvents/Pages/DisplayNews.aspx?NewsID=26913&amp;LangID=E">
                       <strong>
                        Palestine
                       </strong>
                      </a>
                      The High Commissioner presented to the Human Rights Council thee reports concerning the human rights situation in Palestine and other occupied Arab territories.
                      <br/>
                     </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="standard_carrousel_element mt2">
                     <div dir="ltr">
                      <a class="ressource__titlelink big bl mh2-7e m0 aligntop" href="/EN/NewsEvents/Pages/DisplayNews.aspx?NewsID=26898&amp;LangID=E">
                       <strong>
                        Women in public life
                       </strong>
                      </a>
                      At an event organised by the Commission on the Status of Women, the High Commissioner made a series of recommendations to fast-track the full and equal participation of women, in all their diversity, in public life – "for everyone's benefit"
                      <br/>
                     </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="standard_carrousel_element mt2">
                     <div dir="ltr">
                      <a class="ressource__titlelink big bl mh2-7e m0 aligntop" href="/EN/NewsEvents/Pages/DisplayNews.aspx?NewsID=26897&amp;LangID=E">
                       <strong>
                        Slavery
                       </strong>
                      </a>
                      Terming the trans-Atlantic slave trade "a systematic attack against Africans, and a disgrace to humanity as a whole," the High Commissioner called on all stakeholders to "explore more deeply the contemporary consequences of the slave trade – including the evidence so starkly reflected in the unequal impacts of COVID-19"
                      <br/>
                     </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="standard_carrousel_element mt2">
                     <div dir="ltr">
                      <a class="ressource__titlelink big bl mh2-7e m0 aligntop" href="/EN/NewsEvents/Pages/DisplayNews.aspx?NewsID=26893&amp;LangID=E">
                       <strong>
                        Music for Rights
                       </strong>
                      </a>
                      At the International Human Rights Film Festival in Geneva, the High Commissioner hailed an "orchestra of voices"put together by Max Richter and Yulia Mahr, that "speaks to us of eternal and universal values – principles which are essential to the existence of humanity and the purpose of our lives".
                      <br/>
                     </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="standard_carrousel_element mt2">
                     <div dir="ltr">
                      <a class="ressource__titlelink big bl mh2-7e m0 aligntop" href="/EN/NewsEvents/Pages/DisplayNews.aspx?NewsID=26888&amp;LangID=E">
                       <strong>
                        Racism
                       </strong>
                      </a>
                      The entrenched harms caused by racism over generations have been magnified "and brought into lacerating focus" by COVID-19, Deputy High Commissioner Nada Al-Nashif told the Human Rights Council – calling for "leaders who can inspire the transformation of our manifestly dysfunctional systems and norms".
                      <br/>
                     </div>
                    </div>

                       <strong>
                        Venezuela
                       </strong>
                      </a>
